    <!-- Chosen Palette: Warm Neutrals -->
    <!-- Application Structure Plan: The SPA is designed as a top-to-bottom narrative scroll, guiding the user through the project's story. It starts with a hero section to define the product, followed by an interactive visualization of "The Problem". The core is "The Solution," an interactive demo simulating the app's workflow, using a Chart.js chart to visually compare travel times. This is followed by a "Key Features" section using an interactive grid, and a "Future Roadmap" timeline. This thematic, linear structure is more engaging than a static report and allows users to understand the project's value proposition step-by-step, culminating in a clear call to action. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 
        - The Problem: Goal is to compare unfair vs. fair meeting points. A side-by-side visual layout with simple HTML/CSS animations is used to illustrate the disparity in travel times, which is more intuitive than text alone.
        - The Solution (Demo): Goal is to showcase the app's core function. An interactive, multi-step demo is used. Report Info (Venue suggestions with travel times) -> Viz/Method (A horizontal bar chart via Chart.js) -> Interaction (User clicks through steps) -> Justification (The bar chart provides an immediate, clear visual comparison of travel time equity, which is the core value proposition).
        - Key Features: Goal is to present features concisely. An interactive icon grid is used. Clicking an icon reveals details, saving space and encouraging user engagement.
        - Future Roadmap: Goal is to show project evolution. A clickable HTML/CSS timeline is used to present phased development in a clear, chronological, and interactive manner.
    -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
